description.narrative: Global databases on child protection and development were updated and expanded. New global database on children with disabilities has been created, with disaggregated data across 100 indicators, to be released in December 2020. Advanced methodological work for the development of data collection and analytical tools on children with disabilities, adolescent empowerment and participation, and children in residential care. Technical assistance provided to over 30 country offices. Over twenty blogs, articles and reports on child protection and development were released between January and August, and widely used for advocacy, planning and reporting purposes. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/06/2020
